abitats from Panama to central Bolivia. Previously known by only four<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><br class=\"\">species, systematic revisions provided great increase in genus species richness&nbsp;…</div><div style=\"width: auto;\" class=\"\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"\"><tbody class=\"\"><tr class=\"\"><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/citations?hl=en&amp;update_op=email_library_add&amp;info=6NMvl8RMYOgJ&amp;citsig=AMD79ooAAAAAY2H-7LMiPeYD1tDgENt7zTZU-uYU3XRq\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px 4px 0px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Save\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/save-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=tw&amp;url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/14772000.2021.1980449&amp;rt=Three+new+species+of+spiny+mice,+genus+Neacomys+Thomas,+1900+(Rodentia:+Cricetidae),+from+Brazilian+Amazonia&amp;scisig=AAGBfm11DCSyVCZjPIKkXX9GKzXxsz6Npw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Twitter\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/tw-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=in&amp;url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/14772000.2021.1980449&amp;rt=Three+new+species+of+spiny+mice,+genus+Neacomys+Thomas,+1900+(Rodentia:+Cricetidae),+from+Brazilian+Amazonia&amp;scisig=AAGBfm11DCSyVCZjPIKkXX9GKzXxsz6Npw\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"LinkedIn\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/s