><br class=\"\">reviewed and shown to comprise 11 genera and 60 species+ 1 dubious species.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><br class=\"\">Two genera and seven species are described here as<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><b class=\"\">new<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></b>to science: Alineuma&nbsp;…</div><div style=\"width: auto;\" class=\"\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"\"><tbody class=\"\"><tr class=\"\"><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/citations?hl=en&amp;update_op=email_library_add&amp;info=b9gy5FCyclYJ&amp;citsig=AMD79ooAAAAAY2H-7Ii0hFQ3qqkeR2MqRkKTLRHveFJp\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px 4px 0px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Save\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/save-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=tw&amp;url=https://www.biotaxa.org/Zootaxa/article/view/zootaxa.5060.1.1&amp;rt=The+millipede+family+Diplomaragnidae+Attems,+1907+in+the+Asian+part+of+Russia,+with+the+descriptions+of+two+new+genera+and+seven+new+species+(Diplopoda,+Chordeumatida)&amp;scisig=AAGBfm0MwMRYxxL5_CHhd0srOszw6ZBbPA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Twitter\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/tw-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=in&amp;url=https://www.biotaxa.org/Zootaxa/article/view/zootaxa.5060.1.1&amp;rt=The+millipede+family+Diplomaragnidae+Attems,+1907+in+the+Asian+part+of+Russia,+with+the+descriptions+of+two+new+genera+and+seven+new+species+(Diplopoda,+Chordeumatida)&amp;scisig=AAGBfm0MwMRYxxL5_CHhd0srOszw6ZBbPA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"LinkedIn\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/in-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=fb&amp;url=https://www.biotaxa.org/Zootaxa/article/view/zootaxa.5060.1.1&amp;rt=The+millipede+family+Diplomaragnidae+Attems,+1907+in+the+Asian+part+of+Russia,+with+the+descriptions+of+two+new+genera+and+seven+new+species+(Diplopoda,+Chordeumatida)&amp;scisig=AAGBfm0MwMRYxxL5_CHhd0srOszw6ZBbPA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Facebook\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/fb-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br class=\"\"><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin: 0px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_url?url=https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/pre-prints/content-2100006&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;d=18014335097563085259&amp;ei=bMuAYazwCdmUy9YP8vmowAQ&amp;scisig=AAGBfm0-EytDIbnUVlJqONncz83g-K0caA&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;hist=4Z5WABAAAAAJ:10723257300403118941:AAGBfm1inOhnN8aL2qOe-0quNlsVtMjmhA&amp;html=&amp;folt=kw\" class=\"gse_alrt_title\" style=\"text-decoration: none; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(26, 13, 171);\">Three<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><b class=\"\">New Species<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></b>of Neocalyptrocalyx (Capparaceae) for South America</a></h3><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 102, 33);\" class=\"\">J Luber, X Cornejo, TT Carrijo, V de Freitas Mansano&nbsp;- Systematic Botany, 2021</div><div class=\"gse_alrt_sni\">Neocalyptrocalyx (Capparaceae) is a Neotropical genus that comprises eleven<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><br class=\"\">species that occur in the lowlands of Brazil, Guyana, French Guyana, Suriname,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><br class=\"\">Venezuela, and Ecuador. The study of collections deposited in herbaria added to&nbsp;…</div><div style=\"width: auto;\" class=\"\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"\"><tbody class=\"\"><tr class=\"\"><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/citations?hl=en&amp;update_op=email_library_add&amp;info=y3kZw1PG__kJ&amp;citsig=AMD79ooAAAAAY2H-7PeG-ZwnegCbSehu1HErcWyoaX1k\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px 4px 0px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Save\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/save-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=tw&amp;url=https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/pre-prints/content-2100006&amp;rt=Three+New+Species+of+Neocalyptrocalyx+(Capparaceae)+for+South+America&amp;scisig=AAGBfm2hTXwBcA8rTlH_LfaABXTJKGm1YA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Twitter\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/tw-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=in&amp;url=https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/pre-prints/content-2100006&amp;rt=Three+New+Species+of+Neocalyptrocalyx+(Capparaceae)+for+South+America&amp;scisig=AAGBfm2hTXwBcA8rTlH_LfaABXTJKGm1YA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"LinkedIn\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/in-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td><td style=\"padding-right: 4px;\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_share?hl=en&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;ss=fb&amp;url=https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/pre-prints/content-2100006&amp;rt=Three+New+Species+of+Neocalyptrocalyx+(Capparaceae)+for+South+America&amp;scisig=AAGBfm2hTXwBcA8rTlH_LfaABXTJKGm1YA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px;\" class=\"\"><img alt=\"Facebook\" src=\"https://scholar.google.ca/intl/en/scholar/images/1x/fb-32.png\" border=\"0\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\" class=\"\"></a></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br class=\"\"><h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin: 0px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20px;\" class=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(26, 13, 171); vertical-align: 2px;\" class=\"\">[PDF]</span><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/scholar_url?url=https://zookeys.pensoft.net/article/72596/download/pdf/&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;d=13225604711119307064&amp;ei=bMuAYazwCdmUy9YP8vmowAQ&amp;scisig=AAGBfm1mpxYU9_2ctzNFUqN_tDoCQMaXYw&amp;oi=scholaralrt&amp;hist=4Z5WABAAAAAJ:10723257300403118941:AAGBfm1inOhnN8aL2qOe-0quNlsVtMjmhA&amp;html=&amp;folt=kw\" class=\"gse_alrt_title\" style=\"text-decoration: none; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(26, 13, 171);\">A<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><b class=\"\">new species<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></b>of Petta (Annelida, Pectinariidae), with comments on Petta assimilis McIntosh, 1885</a></h3><div style=\"color: rgb(0, 102, 33);\" class=\"\">J Zhang, P Hutchings&nbsp;- ZooKeys, 2021</div><div class=\"gse_alrt_sni\">Abstract The genus Petta Malmgren, 1866 is a small